		analysis: "White-label requirements: (1) brand color change: affects buttons, links, active states, focus rings, selected items. ~15 component instances using brand color. (2) logo: config, not code (logo URL in config). (3) corporate font: typeface change affecting entire interface. With tokens: override 3 token families (brand color, logo, font-family). Without tokens: find and replace 15+ brand color usages, change font-family in 30+ components, maintain fork for this client."
		recommendation: "(1) Brand color override (1h): .theme-fidc-client-a { --color-brand-primary: #1a3b5c; --color-brand-primary-hover: #152f4d; --color-brand-primary-active: #10243e; --color-brand-contrast: #ffffff; /* white text on navy */ }. All Button, Link, ActiveNav, FocusRing, SelectedRow: automatically navy. Semantic colors: UNCHANGED. Green success, red error — same across ALL clients. (2) Logo override (30min): config: { fidc_client_a: { logo_url: '/assets/fidc-a-logo.svg', logo_alt: 'FIDC Client A' } }. Sidebar/header component reads config. (3) Font override (1h): .theme-fidc-client-a { --font-family-primary: 'IBM Plex Sans', sans-serif; }. Load IBM Plex Sans (400, 500, 600, 700) for this client. Verify: tabular figures work in IBM Plex Sans (yes — has tnum support). All components: automatically use IBM Plex instead of Inter. (4) Apply: FIDC client A portal root: <body class='density-compact theme-fidc-client-a'>. Both density and theme applied. Zero component code changes. (5) Testing (2h): verify: (a) brand color applied to all interactive elements. (b) semantic colors unchanged (green success, red error). (c) IBM Plex renders correctly at 11-20px compact scale. (d) contrast passes WCAG AA for navy brand color on all backgrounds. (e) logo displays correctly in sidebar. (6) Total effort: 4.5 hours per FIDC client. Not 4.5 weeks. (7) Scale: 10 FIDC clients = 45 hours total. Each client: unique theme file (3-5 token overrides). Same codebase. Zero forks. Maintenance: fix bug once → all clients get fix. (8) Future: FIDC client self-service theme builder: upload logo, pick brand color, select font → preview → apply. Token override generated automatically."
		principlesApplied: ["ax-01", "ax-03"]
		assumptions: [
			"IBM Plex Sans meets TS criteria (legibility at 11px, tabular figures, glyph distinction) — verified: IBM Plex is professional typeface with full feature set",
			"navy (#1a3b5c) on white provides ≥4.5:1 contrast for text — verify: contrast ratio is ~8.5:1 ✓",
			"FIDC clients only need brand customization (not layout/feature) — validate with client requirements",
			"theme file per client is manageable at scale — 10 clients = 10 small CSS files, minimal overhead",
		]
		rationale: "Theme as token layer 2024+. White-label via token override: 4.5 hours per client vs codebase fork (weeks). With 10 FIDC clients: 45 hours total. Without tokens: 10 separate codebases to maintain. Tokens make multi-brand viable, not just possible."
	},
]

