limitations: [
	{
		description: "Token extraction from existing codebase is labor-intensive initial investment (estimated 30h for medium codebase)."
		alternative: "Incremental extraction: when touching component for feature work, extract its tokens (boy scout rule from TD lens). Start with new components: all token-based from day 1. Existing: migrate incrementally over 2-3 months. Or: agent-assisted extraction (agent scans file, proposes token replacements, human reviews)."
		rationale: "Incremental > big-bang. Agent-assisted > fully manual. Either way: extraction pays for itself in first density/theme change."
	},
	{
		description: "MVDS of 10 components may not cover all MVP UI patterns — some screens may need components not yet built."
		alternative: "For uncovered patterns: use raw HTML/Tailwind with token references (tokens.css imported, use var(--*) for values). Not ideal but consistent via tokens. Promote to component when pattern appears 3+ times. Tokens ensure: even non-component UI uses consistent values."
		rationale: "Token coverage > component coverage. 10 components + token-based raw HTML = 95% visual consistency. 10 components alone = 80%."
	},
	{
		description: "Agent may struggle with complex component APIs — MetricCard with 8 optional props may be misused."
		alternative: "Design components with sensible defaults: most props optional. Agent provides minimum (value, label). Component handles everything else via tokens. Fewer required props = less agent error. Provide 2-3 usage examples in docs (copy-paste friendly)."
		rationale: "Component API complexity ∝ 1/agent reliability. Simplest API that covers use cases = best API for AI-native development."
	},
	{
		description: "Density mode tokens assume all components scale well when spacing values change — some layouts may break in compact (text wrapping where it didn't, overflow in constrained containers)."
		alternative: "Test density modes on all key screens after token override. For components that break: add component-specific token override or min-width/min-height constraint. Keep overrides minimal (<10% of components should need them)."
		rationale: "Test in context. Token system handles 90%. Manual fixes for 10%. Fix is component-specific token, not hardcoded value."
	},
	{
		description: "~165 tokens seems like many — developer or agent may be overwhelmed by choice."
		alternative: "Alias tokens are the working set: ~50 semantic tokens that developers/agents use daily. Globals exist but are rarely referenced directly (aliases abstract them). Component tokens: only where alias doesn't fit. Docs: 'Use --color-text-primary for text. Use --spacing-component for padding. Use --font-size-base for body.' Top 10 tokens cover 80% of use. Full reference for edge cases."
		rationale: "50 alias tokens is the practical working set. 95 globals are implementation detail. Agent learns: 10 tokens for 80% of work, references docs for rest."
	},
]

rationale: "Design tokens são a foundation layer que codifica todas as decisões visuais (cor, espaçamento, tipografia, tamanho, sombra, raio) como variáveis consumíveis por componentes, habilitando: density modes, themes, white-labeling, e consistency governada por sistema em vez de disciplina individual. Na Mesh AI-native com solo founder e agentes gerando UI, esta lens operacionaliza: arquitetura de tokens em 3 camadas (Salesforce Lightning 2019, token-driven development 2024+, token as contract 2024+), composição de componentes com primitivos e compounds (Frost 2016, composition over configuration 2023+), density modes via token override (mode as token layer 2024+), themes (light, dark, white-label) via token override (theme as token layer 2024+, semantic preservation 2024+), responsive layout tokens com breakpoints e content priority (breakpoint-responsive 2024+, content priority 2024+), governança de DS para agentes IA com CLAUDE.md + CI + component docs (design system as prompt 2024+, CI as enforcer 2024+), minimal viable design system de 42 horas (MVDS 2023+, invest-as-you-go 2024+), e spacing system com 4px grid e role hierarchy (spacing roles 2023+, spacing and density 2024+). Universal como infraestrutura de design system; específica como constraint system que governa output visual de agentes IA e habilita multi-persona density + multi-brand theming sem duplicação de código."

}
